Macro that renames external calls to standard Erlang format.

Good news: looks like normal Erlang. Calls are still external, code upgrades
function correctly. Due to unique module names, unintentional name collision
are impossible.

Bad news: module being used must be compiled, so no circular references for
you. Also, (using erlang) seems to be buggy.


    EXAMPLE:

    rebar.config:
{deps, 
    [{erl_import,"v0.0.0",
        {git,"git://github.com/amtal/erl_import.git","HEAD"}}]}.

    mymodule.erl:
(include-file "deps/erl_import/include/erl_import.lfe")
(defmodule my_module
  (export (test 0))
  (using lists math)) ; <--

(defun test () 
  ;       \/\/\/
  (list (math:sin 0) 
        (lists:sort '[1 2 3])
        (lists:append '[1 2] '[3 4])
        (lists:append '[[1 2] [3 4]]))


    UNIT TEST:

rebar compile -v;erl -pa ebin -s erl_import_app
